        <tags>Microsoft Visual Studio VisualStudio 2015 VS VS2015 Update</tags>
        <releaseNotes>
Installs Update 1 CTP (version 14.0.24606.0).

The following technology improvements have been made in Visual Studio 2015.1:

  - You can now Edit and Continue to edit code while debugging Windows Store C++ projects.
  - The C# Interactive Window is back in Visual Studio, as well as the command-line C# REPL window.
  - Released scripting APIs that enable you to build and run C# as a script. The scripting APIs are available on GitHub.
  - Released csi.exe, which is a tool that you can use to run a C# script file (.csx) from the Developer Command Prompt.
  - Team Explorer now features a new Pull Requests hub where users can see the list of pull requests that they have created, as well as the pull requests that others have assigned to them.
  - Improved Create Pull Request experience: now, users can publish branches and create pull requests in a single action. 
  - We now have a branch policy that requires associated work items for any pull request.

The following issues have been fixed in Visual Studio 2015.1:

  - Assume that you have an application in Visual Studio 2015. When you reference Win2D package by using Manage NuGet references, and then build the application, build errors occur.

For a list of known issues and workarounds, see [this page](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/5db54450-b622-4284-b902-ee94952bdd58.aspx).
        </releaseNotes>
